cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.DM, cs.IT, cs.CG. 

The paper deals with string algorithms and data structures, which suggests cs.DS as the most likely category. The use of logarithmic factors in the time complexity also points towards cs.CC (computational complexity) and cs.IT (information theory). The paper also involves combinatorial techniques such as difference covers, which suggests cs.DM (discrete mathematics) as a possible category. Finally, the problem of finding maximal-length factors with a given Hamming distance can be seen as a geometric problem in high-dimensional space, which could potentially fall under cs.CG (computational geometry).
